snippet.textDisplay:
Azzy, you can just buy most of those tricks and be a magician.
Azzy, the number mind reading is very simple, It doesn't matter what number you have, cal it X.
X+8 = (X+8)
(X+8) -3 = (X +5)
(X+5) - X = 5
No matter what X is the final number is going to be 5.

You can change it up a bit, using different numbers just keep the end result a positive umber. You can say,

"Add to your number, the number of the month", lets say it is 2,

"and the day of the week, counting Sunday as 1," this would be 1,

"then subtract the hour in the day," suppose it is 1PM,

"now Subtract X"

and you come up with 1, You just need to know that these when used will result in a positive number, just do the math in your head.

Using these sort of things makes it seem even more random because people will think, how could they know it would be a Sunday in February at 1PM that they ware going to do the trick.
If in a building you could work in the floor you are on, or the address if noticeable, the number of people there, whatever any smallish number that falls between 1-50. Just set up the math the right way and know what number you com up with in the end. Working in multiplication and division is more tricky as you have to have them cancel themselves out, but I have seen it done.
